# Calling the LLM layer

## When to use
Editing `src/llm.js`, changing any OpenRouter/DeepSeek call, prompt, json schema, reasoning effort, model, or the per-stage model config; or debugging a 400/401 from OpenRouter.

## Injected knowledge
- **Reasoning effort: never `max`.** DeepSeek V4 rejects `max` with HTTP 400 — its real ceiling is `xhigh`. `callJSON` has a guard that coerces `effort:'max'` -> `'xhigh'` (one-time warn), so a bad config value can't 400. Send only the nested `reasoning` object; never also pass `reasoning_effort`. `src/llm.js:28-29@79fd5d8` (guard added this task).
- **Model + effort are per-stage, configurable in ONE place.** Each of the 6 LLM call sites resolves `{model, effort}` from `stageModel('<stage>')`, NOT a hardcoded slug. Stages: `linkSelector`, `linkExtract`, `nextLink`, `contentSelector`, `articleExtract`, `classify`. Source: `config/models.json` (`default` + per-stage), overridable by env `LLM_MODEL_<STAGE>`/`LLM_EFFORT_<STAGE>` (e.g. `LLM_MODEL_NEXT_LINK`), then `LLM_DEFAULT_MODEL/EFFORT`; `CLASSIFY_MODEL/EFFORT` stay as legacy aliases for the `classify` stage. Resolution in `src/config.js` (`STAGE_KEYS`, `resolveStage`, `STAGE_MODELS`, `stageModel`). **Default of EVERY stage is `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro` + `xhigh`.** (provenance: this task — `src/config.js` stageModel block + `config/models.json`; hashes finalize on commit.)
- **Two-tier is now opt-in, not the default.** The old cost split — Pro+xhigh to derive reusable selectors, Flash+high for per-page fallbacks/pagination — is no longer hardcoded; you opt into it by setting the `linkExtract`/`nextLink`/`articleExtract` (and others) stages to `deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash`+`high` in `config/models.json`. Cost reminder: xhigh is billed as output tokens, so all-Pro+xhigh is expensive per page — tune the cheap stages down if cost matters.
- **Structured output + defensive parse.** Use `response_format` json_schema with `strict:true`, but still parse defensively: full `JSON.parse`, then regex-extract `{...}`, then throw; and validate every result with a zod schema before use. `src/llm.js:44-56,72-76@79fd5d8`. Why: strict is not an absolute guarantee.
- **SDK details.** The `openai` SDK points at the OpenRouter baseURL; in JS it forwards unknown fields (so `reasoning` passes through). Send `HTTP-Referer` and `X-Title` via defaultHeaders; `maxRetries:3` covers 429/5xx. `src/llm.js:13-17@79fd5d8`.
- **Token discipline.** Always `pruneForLLM` and clamp to `MAX_HTML_FOR_LLM` before sending HTML. `src/llm.js:59@79fd5d8`. See fetching-and-extracting for pruning.
- **The `.env` key override gotcha.** `config.js` loads the project `.env` and overrides shell-exported vars, because Node `--env-file` does not override inherited env - a stale exported `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` otherwise shadows the correct one and yields `401 "User not found"`. `src/config.js:8-37@79fd5d8`. Probe a key: `curl -s https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/key -H "Authorization: Bearer <key>"` (200 = valid).

## Evolution
On task completion, persist a new LLM-layer fact here only if an external signal confirms it (a green bounded crawl, a successful API response, or user confirmation). See meta-skill-evolution.
